{
  "stem": "4361.8",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my brother was put in a column death march with a certain Dr.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Kraus, who was a doctor in our town, and the conditions were terrible.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he must have been emotionally completely at his wit's end, and they were marching in the snow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he gave up-- he must have known by then that his little son was not alive, and he must have thought that his wife, whose name was-- is-- Lajchu is not alive, either.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] He knew by then than his parents were not alive.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He-- I don't know what he thought about me, but I'm-- I'm-- this-- this is just conjecture.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So he gave up hope, and he refused to walk and the SS shot him in the snow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This is true.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A man by the name of Dr.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Verner, who was in the same column who did survive.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Dr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Kraus was also shot later on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was an older man.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He could not go.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But my brother just gave up hope.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The irony of it is that while his little boy did not survive-- and I know this directly from his wife, my former sister-in-law, Lajchu, when they were pulled out of the trains and separated, whether it was one of the inmates of Auschwitz, a man or whoever it was came to her and said, don't hold on to your child.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she was a young woman.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She was 25, probably, and she was with her mother, whom I remember as being an elderly woman, a small, fat lady.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she gave the little boy to her mother [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and Lajchu survived.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She came home.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] but my brother did not.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
